  "prompt": "Did Bill Clinton cheat on Hillary? If so, how did Hillary deal with it?",
  "response": "Yes, Bill Clinton had an affair with Monica Lewinsky, a White House intern, which became public in 1998. This affair led to significant personal and political consequences, including his impeachment by the House of Representatives, though he was acquitted by the Senate.\n\nHillary Clinton's response to the affair was complex and evolved over time. Initially, she stood by her husband and famously claimed on national television that the allegations were part of a \"vast right-wing conspiracy\" against them. She continued to support him throughout the impeachment process.\n\nIn her memoir, \"Living History,\" published in 2003, Hillary discussed the affair and its impact on their marriage. She described feeling \"dumbfounded, heartbroken, and outraged\" but also spoke about the process of working through the betrayal and deciding to stay in the marriage.\n\nOver the years, Hillary has spoken more openly about the affair, acknowledging the pain it caused but emphasizing her commitment to their marriage and family. She has also used the experience to discuss broader issues related to infidelity and public life.\n\nIn summary, Hillary dealt with Bill's infidelity by initially defending him publicly, navigating the political fallout, and eventually addressing the personal impact in her writings and public statements, all while choosing to remain in the marriage.",
